      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Carpenters union. which was\nordered by the trades council to va\ncate its room at Central Labor hall,\nhas opened it's Office at 10 Mill street,\ntelephone Main 2200. The carpenters\nare the strongest organized body in\nthe city. and the split occurred In the\ntrades council when they refused to\nendorse the action of the plumbers\nin striking for what they. the carpen-\ntiers, considered exhorbitant wages."
    }
